@node "Install" "Installing KeepWB"

To  install  KeepWB,  just drag the KeepWB icon into your WBStartup drawer.
It works with Workbench and Directory Opus 5 (as Workbench replacement - hi
JonP :).

To  remove  KeepWB,  just  delete  it  from  whereever you put it.  It only
requires  the  commodities.library  which comes with Workbench anyway so no
additional files are required or created.

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Using KeepWB"

KeepWB  just  sits  happily idling on your system doing nothing.  It has no
user  interface,  and  you  communicate  to  it  via  commodities (see your
Workbench manual).  This is done by using Exchange.

On the Exchange window the gadgets do the following:

Active/Inactive:   Enables  or disables KeepWB (once disabled the Workbench
screen  will  be  able  to  close - or at least Workbench will still try to
close Workbench, other programs may still prohibit Workbench from closing).

Show/Hide Interface:  as above.

Remove:  Terminates KeepWB.

There  are  no hotkeys or shortcuts for the program.  If you would like so,
just e-mail @{" me " link "Oondy" 0}.

@endnode

@node "Works" "How KeepWB Works"

All  KeepWB  does  (when  active)  is  open a small window on the Workbench
screen, which remains there until told to go away.

Once  a  non-Workbench  controlled  window  is opened on the Workbench, the
Workbench  screen  cannot close the screen, and since KeepWB creates such a
window, the screen doesn't close.  And that's really all there is to it.

@endnode

